
The main file is regression-test.ss.

To run all the tests, do the following.
Start Petite Chez Scheme:

./petite

Petite Chez Scheme Version 7.4
Copyright (c) 1985-2007 Cadence Research Systems

> (load "regression-test.ss")
beta0 passed
untyped-primitive passed
...


If the log variable in test.ss is set to #t, then latex files
are generated for every test. The latex file contains the
trace of execution. The file name is the
name of the test (the first argument to the test function)
with .tex added to the end.

Here's a summary of what's in all the files:

regression-test.ss	Lots of examples with expected output to test the system.
test.ss			Infrastructure for testing.
simulation.ss		Testing the simulation for the Jack-of-All-Trades principle.
reduce.ss		The reduction rules.
type-check.ss		The type checker, well-formedness checker, and untyped function.
subst.ss		Various kinds of substitution and the uniquify function.
type-rel.ss		Relations on types, such as equality, consistency, etc.
match.ss		The match macro for doing case analysis.
pretty-print.ss		Latex output of types and terms.
